g</span></span></td>\r\n	<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" style=\"width: 402px; height: 22px\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman, times, serif\">Civil Engineering</span></span></td>\r\n	<td height=\"22\" style=\"height: 22px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n	<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" style=\"width: 161px; height: 22px\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman, times, serif\">School of Architecture</span></span></td>\r\n	<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" style=\"width: 402px; height: 22px\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman, times, serif\">Architecture</span></span></td>\r\n	<td height=\"22\" style=\"height: 22px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div style=\"clear: both\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman, times, serif\">&nbsp;</span></span></div>\r\n',0,'',0,10000,'',0,'',0,1,'|0'),(13,'<p>　　<strong>第一步 申请：</strong>向华南理工大学广州学院国际教育与交流中心（IECC）索取《华南理工大学广州学院外国留学生学习申请表》<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>　　<strong>第二步 初审</strong>：申请表和相关申请材料在报名截止日前邮寄或通过电子邮件寄至华南理工大学广州学院国际教育与交流中心。由国际教育与交流中心进行报名者的资格初审<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>　　<strong>第三步 再审：</strong>学校相关领导、相关学院及部门审核申请人材料<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>　　<strong>第四步 寄送：</strong>电子版录取通知书发出后，向申请人确定是否来华的意向，同时开始向省教厅申请办理外国留学人员来华签证申请表（JW201或JW202表）。在电子版录取通知书发出后的一个月内，将录取通知书原件与外国留学人员来华签证申请表原件寄送至申请人。<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>　　<strong>第五步 办证：</strong>被录取者本人持《华南理工大学广州学院录取通知书》、《外国留学人员来华签证申请表》(JW201或JW202)和《外国人体格检查记录》到中国驻外使馆办理来华签证（六个月以上申请X签证，六个月以下申请F签证）。<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>　　<strong>第六步 报到：</strong>被录取者持录取通知书、护照及有效签证、本人登记照片8张，按入学通知书上的日期准时来华南理工大学广州学院国际教育与交流中心报到，并在入境后30天内办好居留申请手续。无故不按时报到即取消其入学资格。确因特殊情况不能在规定日期内报到者，要事先与学校取得联系，获准后方可延期入学。<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>1. Application:</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nStudents applying to study in GCU shall submit the following documents:<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&middot; Scanned copy of passport which is valid during the stay in China<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;Application Form for Foreign Students<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;Supporting documents as required in the Application Form<br />\r\n<br />\r\nApplicants can mail the following documents by post to the IECC (address as shown below) or send scanned copies to the staff email.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>2. Approval of Application</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe application will be examined by GCU and the Department of Education. Once permission is granted, GCU will send the following documents by post:<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;Offer/ Admission Notice<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;JW202 form (Visa Application Form for Study in China)<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;Proof of Accommodation<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>3. Visa Application</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nWith the documentation, students shall be able to apply for a student visa to the Chinese embassy or consulate. For more information, please contact IECC.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>4. Registration</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nStudents must complete the registration procedures regarding paying tuitions, checking in dorm, registering in academic schools, issuing student ID card, applying for resident permit, registration in the police station, etc. For more information, please contact IECC.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n',0,'',0,10000,'',0,'',0,1,'|0'),(14,'<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><a href=\"http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0327/20170327051314552.pdf\">PDF version:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nhttp://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0327/20170327051314552.pdf</a></div>\r\n',0,'',0,10000,'',0,'',0,1,'|0'),(15,'<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0508/20170508033417530.jpg\" style=\"width: 550px; height: 813px;\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0426/20170426031709768.jpg\" style=\"width: 550px;\" /><br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0426/20170426031726801.jpg\" style=\"width: 550px;\" /><br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0426/20170426031753402.jpg\" style=\"width: 550px;\" /><br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0426/20170426031808933.jpg\" style=\"width: 550px;\" /><br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0426/20170426031824608.jpg\" style=\"width: 550px;\" /><br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0426/20170426031848146.jpg\" style=\"width: 550px;\" /><br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0426/20170426031903773.jpg\" style=\"width: 550px;\" /><br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0426/20170426031922947.jpg\" style=\"width: 550px;\" /><br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0426/20170426031938468.jpg\" style=\"width: 550px;\" /><br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0426/20170426032028429.jpg\" style=\"width: 550px; height: 813px;\" /></p>\r\n',0,'',0,10000,'',0,'',0,1,'|0'),(17,'<div style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>　　1. Gain the check-out form from IECC office. Fill in the personal information.</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>　　2. Ask the lady (inspector) on the first floor to do the dorm-facility check. If there is no damage, roommates shall sign on the line to confirm and the inspector will tick in the first box and sign in the right column.</strong></p>\r\n<table align=\"center\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n	<td style=\"width:132px;\">宿舍<br />\r\n	设备验收</td>\r\n	<td style=\"width:256px;\">\r\n	<div style=\"text-align: left;\">□无损<br />\r\n	□有损<br />\r\n	&nbsp;<br />\r\n	&nbsp;<br />\r\n	同宿舍同学签名确认：</div>\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>\r\n	<td style=\"width:81px;\">日期：</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div style=\"clear:both;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">　　If there is damage, please go to the first floor of C5 for the repair department. The repair staff will examine the situation and assess if student shall pay for repairing facilities. S/he will fill in the following column.</p>\r\n<table align=\"center\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n	<td style=\"width:132px;\">\r\n	<div>维修部</div>\r\n	<div>（C5一楼）</div>\r\n	</td>\r\n	<td style=\"width: 255px; text-align: left;\">□免费<br />\r\n	□已收费&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 金额：&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>\r\n	<td style=\"width:76px;\">日期：</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><br />\r\n<strong>　　3. Go to 302 of the administration building (Accommodation Office) to finish the third row.</strong></p>\r\n<table align=\"center\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n	<td style=\"width:132px;\">学生宿舍<br />\r\n	管理中心<br />\r\n	（行政楼302）</td>\r\n	<td style=\"width:255px;\">可办理宿舍水电卡销卡、退款</td>\r\n	<td style=\"width:76px;\">日期：</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>　　4. If you don&rsquo;t have to return the water and electricity card or get refund, this is the end of the check-out procedure. Return the form to the Accommodation Office.</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">　　For returning cards and getting refunds, go to the first floor of A4 (the Utility Service Counter) to finish the fourth row.　　</p>\r\n<table align=\"center\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n	<td style=\"width:132px;\"><strong>水电卡销卡、退款</strong><br />\r\n	后勤处结算大厅<br />\r\n	（A4一楼）</td>\r\n	<td style=\"width:255px;\">旧宿舍水电卡销卡、退款</td>\r\n	<td style=\"width:76px;\">日期：</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><br />\r\n<strong>　　5. Go back to the dorm and insert the water and electricity card to the machine. The machine will read the card into the &ldquo;refund-available&rdquo; mode.</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>　　6. Go back to the first floor or A4 (the Utility Service Center) to get the refunds.</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>　　7. Finish the check-out procedure by returning the completed form to IECC and the Accommodation Office.</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<br />\r\n',0,'',0,10000,'',0,'',0,1,'|0'),(18,'<p style=\"text-align: right;\">(Update: 2017.3)</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>　　1. Prepare documentation</strong>\r\n<p>　　1) Passport-size photo in blue/white background and receipt of taking the photo: go to the photo-taking shop on the business street (the shop named ASUS with a blue brand) and bring the receipt to IECC after taking the photo.</p>\r\n<p>　　2) Passport + copy of visa page and copy of passport page</p>\r\n<p>　　3) Residence Form: from IECC</p>\r\n<p>　　4) Proof of registration: from IECC (if you have went abroad or HK , you need to get the form from police station)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>　　2. Make an online application for resident permit</strong></p>\r\n<p>　　The staff of IECC will make an online application for resident permit and send the applicant an application number. The number is necessary for on-site application.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>　　3. Go in person to submit the documentation</strong></p>\r\n<p>　　Go to the Certificate-Issuing Hall of Huadu District, get a queue number from the reception, wait in the No. 21 Counter, follow the directions and submit all documentation</p>\r\n<p>　　Address: 广州市花都区建设北路185号花都区办证大厅(Bus from school gate: No. 10, No. 712, No. 712a)</p>\r\n<p>　　Upon successfully hand-in of all documents, the staff will issue a receipt which should be kept well and will serve as required document for collecting the passport.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>　　4. Collect the passport 7 working days later</strong></p>\r\n<p>　　Go to No. 21 Counter of the Certificate-Issuing Hall of Huadu District, present the receipt to the staff, follow the directions to pay the fee, collect the passport</p>\r\n<p>　　Address: 广州市花都区建设北路185号花都区办证大厅(Bus from school gate: No. 10, No. 712, No. 712a)</p>\r\n<p>　　*Note:</p>\r\n<p>　　1) The fee for applying the resident permit is 400RMB for a resident permit less than one year, and 800 RMB for more than one year.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>　　5. Update personal file in the police station</strong></p>\r\n<p>　　Applicant who has successfully applied for the resident permit has the responsibility to go to the police station to update the personal file. Staff at IECC will notify the procedure and provide assistance if necessary.</p>\r\n',0,'',0,10000,'',0,'',0,1,'|0'),(19,'<div style=\"text-align: right;\">　　<span style=\"text-align: right;\">(Update: 2017.3)</span></div>\r\n<p>　　According to the laws and regulations of the People&rsquo;s Republic of China, full-time registered students are required to apply for a resident permit <strong>within 30 days upon entry of mainland China</strong>. For short-term international students holding a valid study visa to study at Guangzhou College of South China University of Technology, a resident permit is required when students need to go out of mainland China and come back (including Hong Kong and Macau).<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>　　1. Make an online reservation to do the body-check</strong></p>\r\n<p>　　Fill in the online-reservation form (language, feature selection, time selection and personal information, cellphone number) on the website of Guangdong International Travel Healthcare Center (GDITHC): http://www.gdwbzx.com/Booking/</p>\r\n<p>　　A four-digit code will be sent to the mobile phone via text message. The online reservation is completed after the code is filled in the online reservation system. Afterwards, a text message containing the reservation number will be sent via text message; this text message is important and should be kept well.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>　　2. Do the body-check</strong></p>\r\n<p>　　Bring the passport, copy of passport picture page and the latest Chinese visa page, 5 color photos and at least 600RMB to the GDITHC, fill in and submit the application form, follow the directions to pay for the fee and do the body-check.</p>\r\n<p>　　Address: No. 207 Longkou Xilu (or Longkou West Road), Tianhe District, Guangzhou广州市天河区龙口西路207号</p>\r\n<p>　　*Note:</p>\r\n<p>　　1) It is recommended that applicant go to do the body-check in the morning without having the breakfast since blood test is required.</p>\r\n<p>　　2) Lateness is not acceptable. Applicant who is late shall make the online reservation again.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>　　3. Obtain the result of body-check</strong></p>\r\n<p>　　Go to the GDITHC again in person to obtain the result with the receipt on the day as specified on the receipt<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>　　4. Prepare documentation for residence permit</strong></p>\r\n<p>　　1) Passport-size photo in blue/white background and receipt of taking the photo: go to the photo-taking shop on the business street (the shop named ASUS with a blue brand) (IECC needs the receipt number for online reservation)</p>\r\n<p>　　2) Body-check result</p>\r\n<p>　　3) Passport, copies of visa page and passport picture page</p>\r\n<p>　　4) JW 202 Form (yellow page): from IECC</p>\r\n<p>　　5) Residence Form: from IECC</p>\r\n<p>　　6) Proof of registration: from IECC</p>\r\n<p>　　7) Admission Notice: from the applicant<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>　　5. Make an online application for resident permit</strong></p>\r\n<p>　　The staff of IECC will make an online application for resident permit and send the applicant an application number. The number is necessary for on-site application.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>　　6. Go in person to submit the documentation</strong></p>\r\n<p>　　Go to the Certificate-Issuing Hall of Huadu District, get a queue number from the reception, wait in the No. 21 Counter, follow the directions and submit all documentation</p>\r\n<p>　　Address: 广州市花都区建设北路185号花都区办证大厅(Bus from school gate: No. 10)</p>\r\n<p>　　Upon successfully hand-in of all documents, the staff will issue a receipt which should be kept well and will serve as required document for collecting the passport.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>　　7. Collect the passport 7 working days later</strong></p>\r\n<p>　　Go to No. 21 Counter of the Certificate-Issuing Hall of Huadu District, present the receipt to the staff, follow the directions to pay the fee, collect the passport</p>\r\n<p>　　Address: 广州市花都区建设北路185号花都区办证大厅(Bus from school gate: No. 10, No. 712, No. 712a)</p>\r\n<p>　　*Note:</p>\r\n<p>　　1) The fee for applying the resident permit is 400RMB for a resident permit less than one year, and 800 RMB for more than one year.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>　　8. Update personal file in the police station</strong></p>\r\n<p>　　Applicant who has successfully applied for the resident permit has the responsibility to go to the police station to update the personal file. Staff at IECC will notify the procedure and provide assistance if necessary.</p>\r\n',0,'',0,10000,'',0,'',0,1,'|0'),(20,'<p><strong>　　I. Arrival</strong><br />\r\n<em>　　1. Before departure:</em></p>\r\n<p>　　Please tell the International Education and Communication Center (IECC) about the flight details upon successful booking. Students are recommended to come with peers or in a group. For a group of more than three students, GCU will attempt to provide pick-up service.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>　　2. How to go to Guangzhou College (GCU) campus from the airport?</em></p>\r\n<p>　　Taxi is the fastest way to go to GCU campus from the Baiyun airport. In usual case it takes 40 minutes and costs 70-120RMB. Chinese taxi drivers may not be able to speak English. The following is a message card in English and Chinese to help communicate with the taxi driver.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>　　请载我到：花都区学府路1号华南理工大学广州学院行政楼前</p>\r\n<p>　　I want to go to: Guangzhou College of South China University of Technology (No. 1 Xuefu Road, Huadu District, Guangzhou)<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0426/20170426033653462.jpg\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 99px; float: right;\" /></p>\r\n<p>　　*Note: Unauthorized taxi drivers are personal cars that cost higher prices. For safety, please choose the authorized taxi.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>　　3. Who is the contact person of GCU?</em></p>\r\n<p>　　IECC Office: Miss Candy Huang</p>\r\n<p>　　*Note: Upon arrival at GCU campus, please go to IECC office at Room 412 in the Administration Building for registration and further guidance.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>　　Intl&rsquo; Business School: Miss Yuki Ji</p>\r\n<p>　　*Note: Students of the International Economics and Trade major will study in IBS. Please contact Miss Ji for the courses and other academic affairs.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>　　4. Registration</em></p>\r\n<p>　　Please bring the passport with valid visa, offer letter and other necessary materials if applicable to the IECC office for registration.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>　　II. Accommodation</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>　　1. Room Type</em></p>\r\n<p>　　1) Two-person Ensuite Room: two students sharing a bedroom with toilet and bathroom.</p>\r\n<p>　　2) Four-person Ensuite Room: four students sharing two bedrooms, a toilet and a bathroom. (One student can occupy one bedroom.)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0426/20170426033303369.jpg\" style=\"text-align: center; width: 250px; height: 166px;\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0426/20170426033322976.jpg\" style=\"text-align: center; width: 250px; height: 166px;\" /><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>　　2. Accommodation Fee</em></p>\r\n<p>　　1) Two-person Ensuite Room: 2250RMB per semester per person;</p>\r\n<p>　　2) Four-person Ensuite Room: 1750RMB per semester per person;</p>\r\n<p>　　(A student occupying a bedroom shall pay 3500 RMB per semester)</p>\r\n<p>　　* The accommodation fee shall be paid before or upon arrival in bankcard with Unionpay or wire transfer.</p>\r\n<p>　　* Wire transfer information of GCU:</p>\r\n<p>　　Bank Name: 中国建设银行广州花都凤华支行</p>\r\n<p>　　Beneficiary Account: 44001551511053001022</p>\r\n<p>　　Beneficiary Name：华南理工大学广州学院</p>\r\n<p>　　SWIFT: PCBCCNBJGDX<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>　　3. Room Facilities</em></p>\r\n<p>　　1) Water and electricity are not included. Students need to top up the electricity and water card.</p>\r\n<p>　　2) Washing machines and dryers located on the first floor of C20 dorm.</p>\r\n<p>　　3) Rooms provides bed &amp; mattress, desk and chair. Students can bring or buy pillow &amp; quilt, blanket, bed sheet at the Business Street in campus.</p>\r\n<p>　　4) Cooking is not permitted in the room.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>　　4. Check-in Procedure:</em></p>\r\n<p>　　Register in IECC&rarr;Pay the accommodation fee&rarr;Arrange room&rarr;Obtain the electricity &amp; water card&rarr;Move in&rarr;Purchase bedding<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>　　5. Are the dorms open during winter / summer holiday?</em></p>\r\n<p>　　No, the dorm will be closed.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>　　III. Living in GCU</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>　　1. Student ID Card</em></p>\r\n<p>　　Students will receive a student ID card (20RMB) at the registration. The student ID card can be used in the library, canteens, shops, sports centers, etc. Top-up machines can be found outside canteens.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>　　2. Mobile &amp; Internet</em></p>\r\n<p>　　Students can buy a SIM card at the Business Street inside our campus.</p>\r\n<p>　　With the SIM card, students can apply for internet access in the dorm.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>　　3. Bank:</em></p>\r\n<p>　　There is an ATM machine belonging to China Construction Bank in campus.</p>\r\n<p>　　The nearest bank around campus is the China Construction Bank which student can go by bus.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>　　4. Insurance</em></p>\r\n<p>　　GCU requires students to buy insurance including accident, medical and hospitalization insurance. Students can choose to buy insurance covering their stay in China in the host country or buy the insurance in China with the help of IECC.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>　　5. Transportation</em></p>\r\n<p>　　Outside GCU school gate are bus stops connecting the town center, train stations, shopping malls and underground stations. A single ticket usually costs 2-3 RMB.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>　　6. Enquiry</em></p>\r\n<p>　　If you have questions, please feel free to contact IECC office：</p>\r\n<p>　　Ms. Candy Huang &nbsp; &nbsp; huanghj@gcu.edu.cn &nbsp; &nbsp; Tel：0086-20-36903179</p>\r\n<p>　　Ms. Jiajia Zhang &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; zhangjj@gcu.edu.cn &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Tel：0086-20-3690-3179<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>　　We wish you enjoy the time in GCU!</p>\r\n',0,'',0,10000,'',0,'',0,1,'|0'),(545,'<span style=\"font-size: 16px\"><span style=\"font-family: 宋体\">邀请短期外国专家的手续：<br />\r\n<br />\r\n确定外国专家人选后，须按以下程序办理来华手续：<br />\r\n<br />\r\n1．邀请单位在外国专家来华前30个工作日向国际合作与交流处提交申请并附以下材料：<br />\r\n（1）华南理工大学广州学院短期来华签证申请表（由聘用单位填写）；<br />\r\n（2）外国专家个人简历复印件；<br />\r\n（3）外国专家护照复印件；<br />\r\n（4）外国专家访华日程；<br />\r\n（5）外国专家任职证明（由外国专家国外工作单位出具）<br />\r\n（6）保证书（由聘用单位出具，内容包括被外国专家在华期间产生的所有费用能够得到有效保证，聘请单位将敦促、监督外国专家遵守中国法律、法规并按时离境。）<br />\r\n（7）如有随行家属（配偶及18岁以下子女），须提供其护照复印件、配偶提供婚姻关系证明、18岁以下子女提供出生证明。<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2．国际教育与交流中心审核后，报主管校领导审批及签发&ldquo;被授权单位邀请函&rdquo;。<br />\r\n<br />\r\n3．邀请单位将&ldquo;被授权单位邀请函&rdquo;原件交外国专家，由外国专家持该函件到中国驻所在国使领馆申请来华签证。</span></span>',0,'',0,10000,'',0,'',0,1,'|0'),(24,'<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-indent: 2em; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\"><br />\r\n<strong>学校位置：台北、新竹</strong><br />\r\n<strong style=\"line-height: 28.8px; text-indent: 2em;\">学校网址：http://www.cute.edu.tw</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-indent: 2em; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>学校简介：</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 中国科技大学创立于1965年，以优质教学型大学自我定位，该校兼重专业教育、通识教育与品格教育，积极实施职涯及实业导向之「系本位课程」，辅导学生成为专业应用人才。于全校师生同仁的努力之下，办学绩效卓越，历次评鉴成绩名列前矛，并于2006~2012年连续七年获得教育部门「教学卓越计划」奖励共21,610万元。重视学生的求职竞争力以及专业职能认证，辅导学生考取证照已有多年经验，并积极帮助同学提升可携式职业能力，为学生在求职路上抢得先机！<br />\r\n该校分别设有台北校区以及新竹校区，台北校区位于市中心附近，至101大楼、信义计划区仅20分钟，校区外设有捷运万芳站，交通极为便利。新竹校区环境清雅，离火车站仅１０分钟，并设有两校区的专车接车接驳，让学生能认真于新竹学习，也能轻易的感受台北的活力。<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>合作项目：</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 两校已于2010年9月签署《学术交流与合作意愿书》，缔结姐妹学校。从2011年至今共有56名学生赴中国科技大学进行一学期的研习交流。同时，两校已开展建筑、土木专业联合培养项目。</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-indent: 2em; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\"><a style=\"color: rgb(64, 64, 64);\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0509/20170509034317812.png\" style=\"width: 650px; height: 296px;\" /></a></p>\r\n',0,'',0,10000,'',0,'',0,1,'|0'),(32,'&nbsp;各二级学院：<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 根据学校与台湾金门大学签署的合作协议，台湾金门大学将在2017年秋为我校学生提供2名免对方学费的公派交换生，赴该校学习一学期（半年）。<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 一、申请对象、相关费用及基本报名要求<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;1.对象：2015级和2016级在校本科生。由于金门大学专业设置与我校外国语学院、管理学院、电子信息工程学院课程较为对口，因此会优先考虑上述学院的学生；但若其他学院认同金门大学的课程并可顺利进行转学分，也同意学生报名。<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 由于学生赴台研习涉及课程对接、学分转换等事宜，因此报名同学可通过金门大学网站自行查找相关专业的课程设置情况，台湾金门大学网址：http://select.nqu.edu.tw/kmkuas<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 2.相关费用：学生赴台期间正常缴纳华广学费和住宿费，无需缴纳金门大学学费；其他费用如：机票费、办证服务费、金门大学住宿费（2000人民币/学期）及个人消费由学生自理。<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;3.公派交换生基本报名要求<br />\r\n　 &nbsp; (1)学习成绩优良，综合素质优秀，在上一学年综合测评中获得二等奖学金或以上。同等条件下，优先考虑参加过与台湾一周文化交流活动的学生。<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (2)对拟派学校有基本了解，有明确的学习方向及个人发展规划。<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;4.境外学习时间：2017年9月-2018年1月。<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;二、报名时间和批准程序<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;1.报名时间： 2017年4月18日&mdash;26日。请各二级学院接到通知后，尽快向学生传达通知内容，立即组织学生自愿报名并按要求提交以下相关材料。<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; （1）华工广州学院学生赴金门大学一学期交流学习申请表(见附件1) ；<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; （2）国（境）外高校联合培养课程学分转换（认定）申请表(见附件2)；<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; （3）中文个人简历一份；<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; （4）中文个人陈述(本人所具备的专业优势、性格特点、研修学习计划、拟达到的目的等)一份（500-800字）；<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; （5）历年成绩单(盖有教务处公章)一份;<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 2.请各二级学院于4月26日上午 11点前确定本学院报名学生的初步名单，将学生报名统计表(附件3)盖章纸质版、电子版和学生材料一并报送至国际教育与交流中心，地址：行政楼412室，电话：36903177，联系人：王老师，邮箱：wangyn@gcu.edu.cn。<br />\r\n　　3.学生处、教务处和国际教育与交流中心接到二级学院提交的名单后将联合进行审核和面试，经筛选和择优后确定公派学生名单，上报校领导审核批准。<br />\r\n　　4.学校于2017年5月12日前对入选名单进行公示。<br />\r\n　　5.学校对确认公示无异议的学生进行发文，按文件要求办理相关手续。<br />\r\n　　6.学校于2017年9月初派出学生至金门大学学习。<br />\r\n<strong>三、管理</strong><br />\r\n　　1.公派交换生若在规定期限内未能获得前往台湾地区的入境许可，学校将撤销该生的交流资格：<br />\r\n　　2.公派交换生，必须按交流计划参加交流项目。在项目期内因故中止项目工作，需经学校同意。<br />\r\n　　3.公派交换生须在项目初期、中期和后期主动向国际交流中心报告交流进展情况和交流心得。交换结束返校后，须向国际交流中心提交《交流总结报告》。在交流过程中如发现派出学生在境外出现违纪违法问题，学校有权随时中止交流。<br />\r\n　　4.国际交流中心负责公派交流生材料的归档工作。<br />\r\n　　5.学生获得公派名额后，将与学校签订《华南理工大学广州学院赴国(境)外交流学习协议书》。<br />\r\n6.公派交换生必须在行前与所属二级学院相关负责人沟通，处理好出境后的学籍管理、课程选读、学分互认等相关事宜。<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n附件：1.华工广州学院学生赴台湾金门大学一学期交流学习申请表<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 2.华工广州学院全日制本科生赴境外高校联合培养课程学分转换（认定）申请表<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 3.各二级学院学生赴台湾金门大学一学期交流学习名单汇总表<br />\r\n&nbsp;<a href=\"http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0424/20170424050929230.doc\">http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0424/20170424050929230.doc</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0424/20170424050929130.xls\">http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0424/20170424050929130.xls</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0424/20170424050930641.xls\">http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0424/20170424050930641.xls</a><br />\r\n　\r\n<div style=\"text-align: right;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;国际教育与交流中心<br />\r\n2017年4月18日</div>\r\n',0,'',0,10000,'',0,'58|59|60|61',0,1,'|0'),(33,'<strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\">学校位置：台湾省台南县</strong><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\" />\r\n<strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\">学校网址：</strong><strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\">www.ksu.edu.tw</strong><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\" />\r\n<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\">&nbsp;</span><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\" />\r\n<strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\">学校简介：</strong><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\" />\r\n<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 崑山科技大学创立于1965年秉持校训「坚毅诚朴」的基本精神，以塑造学生诚恳质朴的人格特质、培育学生具备坚毅执着的为学研究与精进技能的基本态度；首创研发团队培育模式，2004~2008年共执行140件产学合作案，同时积极的推动国内外产学合作，目前已与日本、俄罗斯、印度、美国等国合作，实际配合产业趋势，与企业共同创新。2010根据1111人力银行调查，崑山科技大学为「企业最爱进用新鲜人校系排名」名列台湾私立技职院校第二名。显示崑山人拥有高度的竞争优势。</span><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\" />\r\n<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\">&nbsp;</span><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\" />\r\n<strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\">合作项目：</strong><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\" />\r\n<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 两校于2010年5月签署《学术交流与合作意愿书》，缔结姐妹学校。从2010年9月至今，共有56名学生赴崑山科技大学进行为期一学期的研习交流；同时，截止2014年4月，共有3名教师赴崑山科技大学攻读博士学位。</span><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\" />\r\n<br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\" />\r\n<a style=\"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://communi.chenyimin.cn/uploadfile/2017/0509/20170509034235152.png\" style=\"width: 650px; height: 252px;\" /></a>',0,'',0,10000,'',0,'58|59|60|61',0,1,'|0'),(34,'&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 学校与香港、澳门地区数所高校建立校级合作项目，推荐我校优秀毕业生赴合作高校攻读硕士学位，学生被录取后即可享受相应学费优惠政策。 &nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n',0,'',0,10000,'',0,'58|59|60|61',0,1,'|0'),(172,'<strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\">Dear teachers:</strong><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\" />\r\n<br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\" />\r\n<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\">The State Administration of Foreign Experts Affairs P.R.China has launched an activity called &nbsp;&quot;</span><em style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\">China in the Eyes of Foreign Teachers</em><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\">Photo Exhibition&quot;. All schools and relevant units are welcomed to actively organize foreign teachers to participate in the photo exhibition &amp; competition. The details and requirements are listed as below:</span><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\" />\r\n<br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\" />\r\n<strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\">1. Candidates</strong><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\" />\r\n<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\">1）Schools or institutions nationwide that employ foreign teachers.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\" />\r\n<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\">2）School teachers and students, all foreign teachers work or used to work in China.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\" />\r\n<br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\" />\r\n<br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\" />\r\n<strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\">2. Requirements</strong><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\" />\r\n<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\">Entries must be original, close to life, revealing the spirit of the times, and highlighting friendships among each other. No specific requirements on the themes of the entries. Plagiarism is not allowed and no violations of China&rsquo;s related laws and regulations. The hosts of the activity have rights to editing, publishing and releasing all the entries through outlets such as newspapers, magazines, books and the internet.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\" />\r\n<br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\" />\r\n<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 微软雅黑, 宋体, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28.8px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);\">1)&nbsp;&nbsp; Theme of essay: mainly about what foreign teachers have seen, heard and experienced in China, or stories and friendship among teachers, s